# Exclude shell scripts and agent/SpecKit tooling scaffolding from GitHub
# language statistics (linguist) — small Rust crates otherwise report Shell
# as the primary repository language.
*.sh linguist-detectable=false
.specify/** linguist-vendored
.codex/** linguist-vendored
.claude/** linguist-vendored

# Force LF for Biome-formatted frontend sources regardless of platform
# autocrlf. Biome's formatter normalizes to LF (formatter.lineEnding
# default); Windows checkouts otherwise convert to CRLF on the fly and
# every file trips `biome format --check` there only (blobs stay LF).
*.ts text eol=lf
*.tsx text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.jsx text eol=lf

# Biome validates its own config file's formatting as part of `biome
# format .` (self-referential), so it needs the same LF treatment even
# though it's JSON, not a source file the formatter otherwise touches.
apps/desktop/biome.json text eol=lf

# Generated design-token artifacts and their inputs. `build-tokens.mjs --check`
# compares the committed file byte-for-byte against a freshly generated string,
# which is always LF. Without this a Windows checkout converts these to CRLF and
# the gate fails there — and only there — with a misleading "out of date" that
# tells you to rebuild a file which is already correct.
*.css text eol=lf
apps/desktop/tokens/*.json text eol=lf

# Migration SQL and Rust test files must use LF so that the frozen baseline
# checksum (SHA-384 of file bytes) is identical on all platforms.
*.sql text eol=lf
*.rs text eol=lf
